args: Our friends from the Halidom have\nreturned with the girl and the phantom\nthief, Mr. Radelle.
Bring both of the women to me.\nOur Halidom friends are dismissed.

Aisha, your little escapade has cost me
quite a bit of money, and I will have my
compensation—I don't think you're ever
going to see your home again.
Rather than scowling in silence,\nperhaps you should apologi... Hmm?
Quite the thing to say, seeing how you\nkidnapped her so you could get your\nmeaty paws on the ruin's treasure.
So Aisha told you about that, did she?\nIn that case, it won't do to simply\nturn you over to the proper authorities.
On the other hand, I've heard and seen\na great deal of you lately, and find myself\nquite impressed with your work.
So as a show of respect, I will offer you\na choice: You can come work for me,\nor I can kill you where you stand.
Alas, I don't like either of those choices.\nI only steal what my heart tells me to.

Oh, but I DO owe you one apology.
The treasure in the ruins? It was a special
magic weapon, but it ran amok, so I'm
afraid I had to smash it.
Ah, but do not fret! I brought you back\nsome of the wreckage as a souvenir.\nWould you care to take a look?
Do you have any idea how much that\nwas WORTH, you daft imbecile?!
No clue. But I DO know that I couldn't\nallow it to get loose into the world.
Still, I doubt you wanted it just for your\ncollection room. What WAS your aim?
Money, of course. There would be not a\nshortage of buyers for a unique weapon\nlike that. I could have named my price!
But the ancient documents I took from your\nmansion didn't say what the treasure WAS.\nSo how did you know?
One of my ancestors worked in that lab;\nknowledge of its existence has been\npassed down through my family.
Sadly, they were but a rank-and-file staff\nmember, and lacked the necessary\npermissions to open the door.
Ah, but I do love it when the last\npuzzle piece clicks into place.

Is your question time over already?
I would be happy to keep talking and
give you something to ponder out there
in the great beyond.
Oh, how kind. Well, let us see...\nIs there anything you want to ask moi?
Stop. I've seen more than enough.
That voice is...a man? Who ARE you?!
It seems Lapis and Aisha's explanation\nwas completely true.
Apologies for the ruse, but I really needed\nour dear prince here to see firsthand\njust how truly awful you are.
I'm afraid you're coming with us\nto stand trial.
Hmph. Well, this may be a surprise...\nbut sadly for you, it is not frightening.\nYou DO know where you are, yes?
Oh dear. Surrounded by rough-looking \ncustomers once again. Prince, I dare\nsay it's about that time, don't you think?
For the bomb you gave me? Indeed it is.
My subordinates have already informed\nme about your little ＂light bomb,＂ dear.
So long as we don't look directly at it,\nwe will be fine—and once the light\nsubsides, it is all over for you.
If we were trying to escape, you'd be right.\nBut this time it's just the signal for our\ncounterattack.
Are you ALL from the Halidom?!\nWh-where did you come from?!
Now who's getting forgetful? Your mansion\nis connected to those secret tunnels,\nremember? They've been waiting there.
Oh, and we heard everything ya said\nthrough the walls.
Anyway, looks like yer all pretty\nstunned right now, so...GET 'EM!
Are you still itching for that fight?
I've arranged for Aisha to be taken\nto her village.
The stolen goods from Radelle's mansion\nare being divided up and returned to their\nrightful owners.
Merci! I knew I wouldn't regret mixing\nyou up in all of this.
Radelle has been exposed, Aisha is safe,\nand the stolen goods are being returned.
It is a happy finale for all.
Er, not quite. Now that everything's settled,\nmight I convince you to turn yourself in?
Aisha told me everything—including why\nyou continue the phantom thief's work,\nand the criminal enterprise you're fighting.
But I don't think your methods are right.\nYou cause far too much distress.

I want you to make amends for what
you've done. And in the meantime, we can
continue your work helping victims and
fighting this Noir Magazin.
If I say non, will you attempt to\ntake me in by force?
I know you're not a bad person,\nbut I can't stand by and...
I understand. You are a prince, and must\nembody justice as this world defines it.
Stay true to what you believe,\nand I will do the same.
For I believe the path I've inherited will\nbring joy to this world.
I can't believe I fell for that again...\nHmm? What's this? A card?
Thank you for everything. Though I must say,\nI hate being indebted to people.
So if you ever need aid, but say the word.\n—The Blue Rose
The Blue Rose has left a proclamation!\nWe must protect the treasure!
Things are heating up in here, so I\nsuppose it's time to start the show!
With dignity and beauty, I shall make\nthe impossible possible...
For I am the Blue Rose!
